{
  "texts": [
    "The high entropy feature of alloy can be optimized through the closed-loop optimization, thus ensuring the optimization with high reward with limited experimental resources 58.",
    "The closed-loop optimization workflow involves iterative cycles of material design, synthesis, characterization, and feedback-driven refinement.",
    "Starting from the chemical space of the high entropy alloy, for example the elements in the promising alloy anode, the BO process (Fig. 2d) can be deployed on alloy compositions based on properties like stability, capacity, and conductivity.",
    "These compositions can be synthesized and experimentally evaluated for their electrochemical performance.",
    "The experimental results are then used to update the model, refining its predictions for the next iteration."
  ]
}